# How to force an inventory

## With the HTTP interface

If you agent is running as a service or a daemon, you may be able to access the web interface at <http://localhost:62354>.

If `rpc-trust-localhost` [[configuration key|documentation/agent/configuration]] is true or if `httpd-trust=127.0.0.1`,
a link will be available to force the agent execution.

[[!template  id=warning text="A bug fixed in 2.2.7 prevent the use of `rpc-trust-localhost` and `httpd-trust`."]]

## Command line

You can force an inventory with the [[fusioninventory-agent|documentation/references/agent/2.2.x/fusioninventory-agent]] command.

### Windows

First, you must open a cmd.exe console. Ensure you started with with *Administrator* privilege (*right clic* â†’ *Run as Administrator* on Vista and Seven *Start menu*).

Go in the **c:\Program files\FusionInventory-Agent\perl\bin** (adjust this path depending on your configuration) directory and run:

    # perl fusioninventory-agent

### MacOSX

First, ensure `daemon` key is not defined or false in `agent.cfg`. This key is enabled on MacOSX default settings (`/opt/fusioninventory-agent/agent.cfg`).

Go in /opt/fusioninventory-agent and run the following command

    # cd /opt/fusioninventory-agent
    # ./run.sh 

### Other

Just run:

    # fusioninventory-agent

### Advanced option

You can write a local XML inventory with:

    # fusioninventory-agent --local /tmp

to generate a HTML file instead, add the `--html` flag:

    # fusioninventory-agent --local /tmp --html

Please read [[the fusioninventory-agent reference page|documentation/references]] to get the complet list of supported options.
